  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0dad\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0d91\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0d91\u0db4\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Don't send a penny to Sri Lanka",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Member of Parliament Sarath Fonseka said that Sri Lankans living abroad are requested to refrain from sending money to Sri Lanka as a country where state terrorism is active. He said this while joining the budget debate.",
        "\"We respectfully request Sri Lankans abroad not to send a penny to this country until this state terrorism stops. Even if we are ready to die of hunger, do not send even five cents. Don't help this government.",
        "IMF He said that he will get what he gets from it. We are proud. It's like a beggar got a sweepstakes ticket. But if there is this state trinity, I have a question whether we deserve to receive these or not.\""
      ],
